Robert Penny has been charged with the murder of his wife Margaret Penny and Claire Acocks in Portland, Victoria on May 3, 1991 . 
  The 83-year-old was charged with two counts of murder at Melbourne Magistrates Court on Monday . 
  He was accused of murdering his wife and his mother at a hair salon in Portland . 
  Mr Penny has described the accusations as 'bizarre' He was remanded in custody to appear in court on July 6 . 
 